&gt;So, I want to test a reflexive, associative binary operator (rectangle
&gt;overlap).  I know that for any two valid rectangles A and B:
&gt;
&gt;A * A = A
&gt;A * B = R  // for some overlap result R
&gt;B * A = R  // the same R
&gt;B * B = B
&gt;
&lt;snip /&gt;

&gt;However, this still isn&#39;t trying all four possible tests on each
&gt;fixture.
&lt;snip /&gt;

Abstract Test Case with an implementation for each particular fixture.
Exclude the abstract test case from your test runner (however you run
your tests).

abstract class OverlapTestCase extends TestCase {
    abstract Rectangle makeRectangleA();
    abstract Rectangle makeRectangleB();

    testCommonProperty1() {
        // Use makeRectangle*() to make rectangles
        // assertions...
    }
    ...
}

